<br>
1 - Try this:<br>
 <br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://perso.respublica.fr/fayguardians/Guides/Factions/Factions.html">perso.respublica.fr/faygu...tions.html</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Anezka has a summary guide for many cities<br>
<br>
2 - There are 3 key factions to concern yourself with.  The Freeport Militia (the Guards of West Freeport and the Warriors), the Ashen Order (freeport monks) and the knights of truth (North Freeport Guards and Paladin Guild).  You will need to do both sets of guards to have safe access to the monk guild and the bank<br>
<br>
There is also 2 further factions for merchants, but you can buy from them with sneak, or get basic necessities from the merchant in the Monk guild when you have done monk faction.<br>
<br>
3- You can turn the deathfist belts into the Captain in the Warrior guild on the second floor - can't recall his exact name.  Note that this will WORSEN you faction with knights of truth though.  Paladin and Warrior factions are frequently opposed.<br>
<br>
4- Haven't hunted in the revamped Nekt - can't answer<br>
<br>
5- should do - except he will not be able to trade with normal merchants via sneak and may need to repeat quests or make kills more/less times than the monk.  He will also not be able to use the monk quests to accelerate the time it takes him.<br>
<br>
6- You are talking 100s of orcs to be able to enter town with wolf-form on.  100s more again to do without.<br>
<br>
My advice is this:<br>
<br>
Kill as many orcs as you need to be able to get into town with a wolf form (obtain from a 39+ Druid - ask one nicely).  This is going to take you a LONG time.<br>
<br>
Do the first monk headband quest repeatedly, hand in at least 2 backpacks worth of components).  This quest gives plusses to monk faction and to paladin faction.  Note enough faction to pass the guards safely and not get attacked by the monks in wolf form is not necessarily enough to do the quest.  If it doesnt work go back and kill more orcs.  Note that you can often buy the items for this quest in large volumes either from newbies in WFP or from the ogre or the gnome merchants, who the newbies frequently sell stacks of these items too.<br>
<br>
Do this until you are well liked by both.  You can then do the Warrior guild version of the DF belt quest to sacrifice some of your excess paladin faction for warrior faction until neither is KOS to you.  If you go too far repeat the monk quest some.<br>
<br>
Not the only method but I found the quickest for a monk.  Your troll friend will need to do additional faction work. <p>Tarrask, 49th Swifttail of Saryrn
